		<td><b>Sega Genesis + 32X vs SNES + SD2SNES</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have read many of stories comparing the Sega Genesis to the Super Nintendo, however I haven't really head of comparing upgraded versions of these consoles. <br /><br />When comparing the hardware specs of a standard Genesis and SNES the SNES pretty much takes the cake, but does the 32X have enough weight and does it surpass a stand alone SNES? What about the MSU1 enhancement chip for the SD2SNES? Does the SD2SNES surpass a Genesis with a 32X combined together?<br /><br />Post your thoughts and opinions regarding the upgraded versions of these consoles. What system would out preform the other given the enhancement upgrades?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
