	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Sega Genesis + 32X vs SNES + SD2SNES</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />??? If anything, the MSU-1 is more comparable to the Sega CD. That is, after all, what it was designed to go against. The thing is, no matter how much extra processing power you give a system, it will always be dragged down by it's video hardware. (That's probably the main reason the Sega CD looked so terrible.) The 32x has it's own video hardware and somewhat acts as a pass-through, while the MSU-1 still uses the SNES's video hardware. I agree with psychopathicteen when he said Nintendo should have made a buss that went strait from the cartridge slot to the PPU's, but obviously, they didn't.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


