		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Isn't SD2SNES more comparable to the Mega Everdrive? (and the latter is a moving target thanks to being able to reload its FPGA program on the fly, e.g. the latest firmware adds fast multiplication and division in addition to mapper, SD card and USB support)<br /><br />As far as I know there isn't anything comparable to the 32X on the SNES (probably for good) so don't expect much on this end. Maybe some of the coprocessors can fill some of the gaps though (SuperFX was meant to do this for 3D rendering, for instance). And yes, the 32X can be quite a beast when used properly (see <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UxfsXDBCp3o" class="postlink">Darxide</a>: textured lit polygons... whether the gameplay lives up to it is a different matter =P).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
